| ID           | Validation Requirement                                                   | Control Information                                                                                 | Evidence Examples                                           | Related NIST SP 800-53 Controls     |
|--------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| KSI-SC-01    | Harden and review network and system configurations                      | Automatically collects and monitors system/network configuration baselines, alerts on drift or changes. | Configuration files, review logs, vulnerability scan results | CM-2, CM-4, CM-8                     |
| KSI-SC-02    | Encrypt all network traffic                                              | Continuously verifies TLS/SSL configurations and network encryption in transit.                    | Network traffic encryption configs, certificate reports     | SC-8, SC-8(1), SC-13                 |
| KSI-SC-03    | Encrypt all federal and sensitive information at rest                    | Validates use of approved encryption algorithms and verifies encryption at rest settings.           | Encryption key lifecycle records, audit reports             | SC-12, SC-28, SC-28(1)              |
| KSI-SC-04    | Manage configuration centrally                                           | Tracks centralized configuration management tool outputs and changes.                              | CMDB exports, change logs, configuration management reports | CM-2, CM-4                           |
| KSI-SC-05    | Enforce system and component integrity through cryptographic means       | Verifies cryptographic hashes and signatures for software and system components.                    | Hash verification logs, integrity check reports             | SI-3, SI-4                           |
| KSI-SC-06    | Use a key management capability to execute regular rotation of digital keys | Monitors key rotation schedules and compliance with key management policies.                        | Key rotation logs, KMS reports                              | IA-7, RA-7                           |
| KSI-SC-07    | Use a consistent, risk-informed approach for applying security patches    | Tracks patch management policies and deployment across all systems based on risk prioritization.    | Patch reports, vulnerability assessment outputs             | CM-8                                 |
